How to Use: - Ensure the device is turned off before changing the batteries. - Open the battery compartment of your device. - Check the battery orientation diagram, usually given inside the compartment. - Insert the Tesla AAA Zinc-Carbon Batteries according to the diagram. The flat end is usually the negative side and the raised button end is positive. - Replace the compartment cover and your device is ready to use again. Storage Instructions: - Keep the batteries at room temperature in a dry place. - Avoid extreme temperatures, both hot and cold, as they can reduce the efficiency of the batteries. - Store your batteries in the original packaging until use to prevent accidental activation or short-circuiting. - Always keep batteries out of the reach of children. Check the battery compartment of your device for the battery size and directions for positive and negative placement. 2. Remove the old batteries from your device (if applicable). 3. Align each Tesla battery in the correct position according to the positive (+) and negative (-) indicators. 4. Securely close the battery compartment. 5. Turn your device on to confirm the correct installation. If the device does not turn on, recheck the battery placement. Storage Instructions: 1. Store batteries in a cool, dry place away from metal objects. 2. Ensure the batteries are stored in their original packaging to avoid damage or short circuit. 3. Carbon: Used as the cathode in the battery. 3. Ammonium Chloride: Used as the electrolyte, providing a medium for the flow of electric current. 4. Manganese Dioxide: Mixed with carbon to create the cathode. 5. Steel: Forms the external casing of the battery. Gives the battery durability and strength.
